<chapter xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"  xml:id="chapter-threads">
  <title>Threads and Concurrent Programming</title>
  <introduction>
    <objectives>
     <p>
      After studying this chapter, you will
    </p>
     <ul>
        <li>
          <p>
            Understand the concept of a thread.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Know how to design and write multithreaded programs.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Be able to use the <c>Thread</c> class and the <c>Runnable</c> interface.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Understand the life cycle of a thread.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Know how to synchronize threads.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </objectives>
  </introduction>
